        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-11-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                <head>No. 674.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince Hayti</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 15, 1888</date>. (Received November
                        26.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 220.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Boston</hi>
                    intends leaving here to-morrow morning direct for New York and will communicate
                    immediately with the Navy Department and send full details as to the case of the
                    steam-ship <hi rend="italic">Haytian Republic</hi> and that of the schooner <hi rend="italic">William Jones.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I will forward my report to the Department on these two cases as soon as it can
                    be prepared, as the questions contain a great deal of reading matter.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John E. W. Thompson.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
